  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nDisplay identity requests that can be declined or accepted in the Activity Center.\r\n\r\n![img](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/196445683-829a4bca-7003-42ae-aa05-3232e1d2a9b3.png)\r\n\r\n### Acceptance criteria\r\n\r\n>Given that Alice already accepted a contact request from Carol\r\n>When Alice sends an identity verification to Carol\r\n>Then Carol receives a new notification in her Activity Center\r\n>And the notification message displays the challenge\r\n\r\n>Given that Carol received an identity request from Alice\r\n>Then Carol can either Accept or Decline the challenge\r\n\r\n>Given that Carol received an identity request from Alice\r\n>When Carol declines the challenge\r\n>Then she sees the same notification change its status to \"Declined\"\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\n- There's no need to implement the actual acceptance flow, as this is more complex and can be done using a separate issue. A dummy event handler might suffice.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nAt the moment (2022-10-18), it's necessary to use the unmerged status-go branch https://github.com/status-im/status-go/tree/feature/activity-center-read-unread.\r\n\r\n### Figma\r\n\r\nIdentity request flows are described in https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=639%3A21926.",
