    "body": "> I probably missed smth, but frankly can't understand the purpose of identity requests in case both users are already contacts. Is there any doc/explanation or someone can elaborate on it?\r\n\r\n@churik, I think I'm not the best person to answer your question, but I believe the idea is that some users need to verify certain contacts are who they really think they are, for various reasons.\r\n\r\nImagine, for example (and this is a real case scenario), my smartphone was stolen and the thief starts to communicate with my mom before I get the chance to warn her. My mom would then be able to send an identity challenge to the thief if she thinks something is fishy, and, at least in theory, she would be able to avoid sharing unwanted secrets with the thief.\r\n\r\nI know the above scenario is super edge case for some people, but not here in Brazil. I think there are many other scenarios to justify this feature, **but having said all this, I think the vast majority of users won't care or even know what identity verification even is**.",
